  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6585.45 sitting 14 points below the GEX flip at 6599, dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as they hedge their long gamma positions. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (+85.9B) creates a strong magnet effect that should cap upside moves, while the thick cluster of positive GEX from 6590-6610 forms a consolidation zone where dealers will aggressively fade directional moves. The recent GEX surge combined with PIN regime suggests dealers will be active stabilizers, selling any rally toward 6600 and buying weakness toward the 6560 negative gamma pocket.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to grind higher toward 6600 then get capped there.",
